Dr George Mukhari Hospital and Charlotte Maxeke Academic Hospital have been added as COVID-19 vaccination sites. Courtesy #DStv403 Two new JOHANNESBURG - Dr George Mukhari Hospital and Charlotte Maxeke Academic Hospital have been added as vaccination sites in Gauteng. Gauteng Premier David Makhura and Health MEC Nomathemba Mokgethi were on a walk-about at the Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital on Friday. READ: COVID-19: 1.1m people to be vaccinated by end of March - Mkhize They were there to monitor the progress of the vaccination programme. eNCA reporter Slilindelo Masikane shares more details in the video.